{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882088617,"sessionID":"ses_2852e23b2ffei1TKMPwenTxN23","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad23064001hycPoLxjrjZ0uX","messageID":"msg_d7ad1fd9c001XSOw57jk52mIWr","sessionID":"ses_2852e23b2ffei1TKMPwenTxN23","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-0f9de3a3ca12446d91c26c38bdcc2d46","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n8: | Module | `sdk-python` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Implementation (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` with router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout, connect_timeout\n20:   - Purpose: Initialize HTTP client for Router data plane communication\n21:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n22:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestDataPlaneClientInit -v`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2**: Implement `SESSION_HEADER` class constant `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n25:   - Purpose: Define session header name as class-level constant\n26:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n27:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient; print(AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.SESSION_HEADER)\"`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3**: Implement base_url construction via `urljoin`\n30:   - Purpose: Build base_url as `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n31:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n32:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBaseURLConstruction -v`\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T1.4**: Implement HTTP session with connection pooling (pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)\n35:   - Purpose: Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling\n36:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestConnectionPooling -v`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.5**: Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` method\n40:   - Purpose: GET base_url to bootstrap session, extract session_id from `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n41:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n42:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBootstrapSessionID -v`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T1.6**: Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` missing header handling\n45:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError when `x-agentcube-session-id` header missing in response\n46:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n47:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestBootstrapSessionID::test_bootstrap_missing_header -v`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T1.7**: Implement `invoke()` method with session_id and payload parameters\n50:   - Purpose: POST to base_url with json=payload and session header\n51:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n52:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvoke -v`\n53: \n54: - [ ] **T1.8**: Implement `invoke()` headers with `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n55:   - Purpose: Set both session header and Content-Type on POST requests\n56:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n57:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeHeaders -v`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T1.9**: Implement `invoke()` timeout override logic\n60:   - Purpose: Use passed timeout value or fall back to self.timeout\n61:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n62:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestInvokeTimeout -v`\n63: \n64: - [ ] **T1.10**: Implement `close()` method\n65:   - Purpose: Close the HTTP session connection pool\n66:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n67:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py::TestClose -v`\n68: \n69: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient Implementation (ST-2)\n70: \n71: - [ ] **T2.1**: Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` with agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout\n72:   - Purpose: Initialize high-level client with all configuration parameters\n73:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n74:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestAgentRuntimeClientInit -v`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement Router URL required validation\n77:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError if router_url not provided via arg and ROUTER_URL env var\n78:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n79:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestRouterURLRequired -v`\n80: \n81: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_resolve_router_url()` helper\n82:   - Purpose: Resolve router_url from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n83:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n84:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestRouterURLResolution -v`\n85: \n86: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement session reuse logic when session_id provided\n87:   - Purpose: Skip bootstrap_session_id call when session_id argument is provided\n88:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n89:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestSessionReuse -v`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement session bootstrap via AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n92:   - Purpose: Call dp_client.bootstrap_session_id() when no session_id provided\n93:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n94:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestSessionBootstrap -v`\n95: \n96: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `_init_data_plane()` private method\n97:   - Purpose: Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with router_url, namespace, agent_name\n98:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n99:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestDataPlaneInit -v`\n100: \n101: - [ ] **T2.7**: Implement `__enter__()` context manager method\n102:   - Purpose: Return self for context manager usage\n103:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n104:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestContextManager -v`\n105: \n106: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement `__exit__()` context manager method\n107:   - Purpose: Call close() on context exit (with or without exception)\n108:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n109:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestContextManager::test_context_manager_calls_close -v`\n110: \n111: - [ ] **T2.9**: Implement `invoke()` method with payload and optional timeout\n112:   - Purpose: Delegate to dp_client.invoke with session_id and payload\n113:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n114:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestInvoke -v`\n115: \n116: - [ ] **T2.10**: Implement `invoke()` session_id validation\n117:   - Purpose: Raise ValueError if session_id is None when invoke called\n118:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n119:   - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py::TestInvoke::test_invoke_without_session -v`\