{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882464824,"sessionID":"ses_2852e23b2ffei1TKMPwenTxN23","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad7edd20011JZQx5L6chMZjZ","messageID":"msg_d7ad5846c001tS4Ei9ggRJEr3y","sessionID":"ses_2852e23b2ffei1TKMPwenTxN23","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-8f845dd773e040f39b0eb52d40b8c24c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 |\n| Module | `sdk-python` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: HTTP Session Configuration (ST-1)\n\n- [ ] **T1.1**: Implement `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120` constant in `http.py`\n  - Purpose: Define default read timeout constant\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_TIMEOUT; print(DEFAULT_TIMEOUT)\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.2**: Implement `DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT = 5.0` constant in `http.py`\n  - Purpose: Define default connection timeout constant\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT; print(DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT)\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.3**: Implement `DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS = 10` constant in `http.py`\n  - Purpose: Define default connection pool size constant\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS; print(DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS)\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.4**: Implement `DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE = 10` constant in `http.py`\n  - Purpose: Define default maximum pool connections constant\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE; print(DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE)\"`\n\n- [ ] **T1.5**: Enhance `create_session` to accept `timeout` and `connect_timeout` kwargs\n  - Purpose: Allow custom timeout configuration on session creation\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSessionTimeout -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.6**: Implement `create_session` with default headers parameter\n  - Purpose: Allow setting default headers on session creation\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSessionHeaders -v`\n\n- [ ] **T1.7**: Implement `create_session` with retry configuration parameter\n  - Purpose: Allow configuring retry behavior for transient failures\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestCreateSessionRetry -v`\n\n### Phase 2: Retry Handler Implementation (ST-2)\n\n- [ ] **T2.1**: Implement `RetryConfig` dataclass with `max_retries`, `backoff_factor`, `retry_on` parameters\n  - Purpose: Define retry configuration structure\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryConfig -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG` with `max_retries=3`, `backoff_factor=0.5`\n  - Purpose: Define default retry configuration for transient errors\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.utils.http import DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG; print(DEFAULT_RETRY_CONFIG)\"`\n\n- [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` extending `HTTPAdapter`\n  - Purpose: Custom HTTPAdapter with retry logic\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryHTTPAdapter -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.4**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` retry on 5xx status codes\n  - Purpose: Retry on server errors (500, 502, 503, 504)\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryOn5xx -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.5**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` retry on connection errors\n  - Purpose: Retry on `ConnectionError`, `Timeout` exceptions\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestRetryOnConnectionError -v`\n\n- [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `RetryHTTPAdapter` exponential backoff\n  - Purpose: Implement backoff_factor * (2 ** (retry_count - 1)) delay\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestExponentialBackoff -v`\n\n### Phase 3: HTTP Request Helper Functions (ST-3)\n\n- [ ] **T3.1**: Implement `make_timeout_tuple(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` helper\n  - Purpose: Create requests timeout tuple (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestMakeTimeoutTuple -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `make_timeout_tuple` with default values fallback\n  - Purpose: Use DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT and DEFAULT_TIMEOUT when not specified\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestMakeTimeoutTupleDefaults -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `is_retryable_error(exception)` helper function\n  - Purpose: Determine if an exception is retryable\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestIsRetryableError -v`\n\n- [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `is_retryable_status(status_code)` helper function\n  - Purpose: Determine if HTTP status code is retryable (5xx)\n  - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n  - Verification: `pytest sdk-python/tests/test_http_utils.py::TestIsRetryableStatus -v`\n\n### Phase 4: Session Header Constants (ST-4)\n\n- [ ] **T4.1**: Implement `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` constant\n  - Purpose: Define